<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Consumer - Making Payments</title>
    <link href="css/theme.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/global.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/consumer_making_payments.css">
    <script src="assets/js/i18n.js"></script>
    <style>
        /* Basic reset for preview consistency */
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: sans-serif;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Site Header -->
    <header class="modern-header" id="consumerHeader">
    </header>

    <div class="cmp-page">
        <a href="#cmp-main-content" class="cmp-skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
        <!-- Sidebar Overlay (mobile) -->
        <button class="cgs-sidebar-toggle" id="cgsSidebarToggle" aria-label="Toggle navigation menu"
            aria-expanded="false">
            <i class="fa fa-bars"></i>
        </button>
        <!-- Sidebar overlay -->
        <div class="cgs-sidebar-overlay" id="cgsSidebarOverlay"></div>
        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div id="consumerSidebar">

        </div>
        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="cmp-main">
            <div class="cmp-content-wrapper">
                <main class="cmp-content" id="cmp-main-content">
                    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
                    <nav class="cmp-breadcrumb" id="cmp_breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                        <a onclick="load_page('index')" data-i18n="making_payments.breadcrumb.docs">Docs</a>
                        <span class="separator">/</span>
                        <a onclick="load_page('consumer_docs_home')" data-i18n="making_payments.breadcrumb.consumer">Consumer</a>
                        <span class="separator">/</span>
                        <span class="current" data-i18n="making_payments.breadcrumb.current">Making Payments</span>
                    </nav>
                    <!-- Page Title -->
                    <h1 class="cmp-page-title" id="cmp_title" data-i18n="making_payments.title">Making Payments</h1>
                    <p class="cmp-page-subtitle" data-i18n="making_payments.subtitle">
                        Learn how to make fast, secure payments using the MPay Consumer Wallet. Whether scanning a QR
                        code, showing yours, or tapping with NFC — paying has never been easier. </p>
                    <!-- Payment Method Cards -->
                    <div class="cmp-method-cards">
                        <div class="cmp-method-card">
                            <div class="cmp-method-card-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-qrcode"></i>
                            </div>
                            <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.method_cards.qr.title">QR Code Payments</h5>
                            <p data-i18n="making_payments.method_cards.qr.body">Scan or show a QR code to complete payments instantly at any MPay merchant.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-method-card">
                            <div class="cmp-method-card-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-wifi"></i>
                            </div>
                            <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.method_cards.nfc.title">NFC Tap-to-Pay</h5>
                            <p data-i18n="making_payments.method_cards.nfc.body">Simply hold your phone near the terminal for a contactless payment experience.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!-- Section: Scanning QR Codes -->
                    <section class="cmp-section" id="cmp_content_scan_qr">
                        <h2 class="cmp-section-title" id="scan-qr" data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.heading">Scanning QR Codes</h2>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.intro">The most common way to pay is by scanning a merchant's QR code. This process takes only a few
                            seconds and securely processes your payment through the MPay network.</p>
                        <h4 data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.how_to_title">How to do a Scan to Pay</h4>
                        <p data-i18n-html="making_payments.scan_qr.how_to_intro"><b>Scan to Pay</b> allows users to scan a QR code to quickly send money or make payments
                            using their wallet.</p>
                        <div class="steps">
                            <div class="step">
                                <div class="step-title" data-i18n-html="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.1.title">Tap &quot;Scan to Pay&quot;</div>
                                <div class="step-content" data-i18n-html="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.1.body">From the home screen, tap the <strong>Scan to Pay
                                        icon</strong> in the <b>Send Money</b> section.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step">
                                <div class="step-title" data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.2.title">Scan the Recipient's QR Code</div>
                                <div class="step-content" data-i18n-html="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.2.body">Point your camera at the recipient&apos;s QR code. Once
                                    scanned, the recipient&apos;s details will automatically populated in Scan to Pay
                                    form.&nbsp;</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step">
                                <div class="step-title" data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.3.title">Enter Amount and Confirm</div>
                                <div class="step-content" data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.3.body">Enter the transfer amount, review the details, and confirm
                                    with your PIN or biometric authentication.</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="step">
                                <div class="step-title" data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.4.title">Transfer Complete</div>
                                <div class="step-content" data-i18n-html="making_payments.scan_qr.steps.4.body">You&apos;ll see a confirmation screen with a transaction
                                    <b>reference number.</b>&nbsp;
                                    <p>The recipient is notified instantly.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <ol class="cmp-steps">
                        </ol>
                        <!-- QR Scanner Visual -->
                        <div class="cmp-qr-visual" aria-hidden="true">
                            <div class="cmp-phone-mockup">
                                <div class="cmp-phone-screen">
                                    <div class="cmp-phone-notch"></div>
                                    <div class="cmp-qr-scanner">
                                        <div class="cmp-qr-corner top-left"></div>
                                        <div class="cmp-qr-corner top-right"></div>
                                        <div class="cmp-qr-corner bottom-left"></div>
                                        <div class="cmp-qr-corner bottom-right"></div>
                                        <div class="cmp-qr-scan-line"></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="cmp-qr-label" data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.visual_label">Align QR code within frame</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-callout info">
                            <div class="cmp-callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-callout-body">
                                <strong data-i18n="making_payments.scan_qr.tip_title">Tip: Quick Pay Shortcut</strong>
                                <p data-i18n-html="making_payments.scan_qr.tip_body">You can also launch the QR scanner directly by double-tapping the MPay icon on your
                                    home screen, or by using the "Scan" shortcut from the notification shade widget.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Section: Showing Your QR Code -->
                    <section class="cmp-section" id="cmp_content_show_qr">
                        <h2 class="cmp-section-title" id="show-qr" data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.heading">Showing Your QR Code</h2>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.intro">Some merchants prefer to scan your QR code using their terminal or device. In this case, you
                            simply present your personal payment QR code for them to scan.</p>
                        <h4 data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.how_to_title">How to Show Your QR</h4>
                        <ol class="cmp-steps">
                            <li class="cmp-step">
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">1</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-content">
                                    <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.steps.1.title">Open Your Payment Code</h5>
                                    <p data-i18n-html="making_payments.show_qr.steps.1.body">Tap <strong>"Pay"</strong> on the home screen, then select <strong>"Show My QR
                                            Code"</strong>. Your personal payment QR code will be displayed.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="cmp-step">
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">2</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-content">
                                    <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.steps.2.title">Present to Merchant</h5>
                                    <p data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.steps.2.body">Hold your phone steady with the QR code visible. The merchant will scan it using
                                        their MPay Merchant terminal or device camera.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="cmp-step">
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">3</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">3</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-content">
                                    <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.steps.3.title">Confirm on Your Device</h5>
                                    <p data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.steps.3.body">After the merchant scans and enters the amount, you'll receive a push
                                        notification. Confirm the payment amount and authenticate to complete.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        <!-- QR Code Display Visual -->
                        <div class="cmp-qr-visual" aria-hidden="true">
                            <div class="cmp-phone-mockup">
                                <div class="cmp-phone-screen">
                                    <div class="cmp-phone-notch"></div>
                                    <div class="cmp-qr-code-display"></div>
                                    <div class="cmp-qr-label" data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.visual_label">Show this to merchant</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-callout warning">
                            <div class="cmp-callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-callout-body">
                                <strong data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.security_title">Security Note</strong>
                                <p data-i18n="making_payments.show_qr.security_body">Your payment QR code refreshes every 60 seconds for security. Never share a
                                    screenshot of your QR code. Only show it at the point of sale when making a payment.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Section: NFC Tap-to-Pay -->
                    <section class="cmp-section" id="cmp_content_nfc_tap">
                        <h2 class="cmp-section-title" id="nfc-tap" data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.heading">NFC Tap-to-Pay</h2>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.intro">If your device supports NFC and the merchant has an NFC-enabled terminal, you can pay by
                            simply tapping your phone against their payment device — no scanning needed.</p>
                        <h4 data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.how_to_title">How to Use NFC Payments</h4>
                        <ol class="cmp-steps">
                            <li class="cmp-step">
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">1</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-content">
                                    <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.1.title">Enable NFC</h5>
                                    <p data-i18n-html="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.1.body">Ensure NFC is enabled in your phone settings and in the MPay app under
                                        <strong>Settings → Payment Methods → NFC Payments</strong>.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="cmp-step">
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">2</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-content">
                                    <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.2.title">Hold Near Terminal</h5>
                                    <p data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.2.body">When the merchant's terminal shows the amount, hold the back of your phone (near
                                        the NFC antenna) within 4cm of the payment terminal.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="cmp-step">
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">3</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-content">
                                    <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.3.title">Authenticate</h5>
                                    <p data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.3.body">A vibration or tone confirms the connection. Authenticate using biometrics or
                                        your PIN. The payment processes in under 2 seconds.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li class="cmp-step">
                                <div class="cmp-step-number">4</div>
                                <div class="cmp-step-content">
                                    <h5 data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.4.title">Payment Complete</h5>
                                    <p data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.steps.4.body">You'll see a success checkmark and receive both an in-app notification and
                                        optional SMS receipt.</p>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                        <!-- NFC Visual Animation -->
                        <div class="cmp-nfc-visual" aria-hidden="true">
                            <div class="cmp-nfc-device">
                                <div class="cmp-nfc-icon-container">
                                    <i class="fa fa-mobile-alt"></i>
                                    <div class="cmp-nfc-wave"></div>
                                    <div class="cmp-nfc-wave"></div>
                                    <div class="cmp-nfc-wave"></div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-nfc-label" data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.visual_phone">Your Phone</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-nfc-arrow">
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-nfc-device">
                                <div class="cmp-nfc-icon-container">
                                    <i class="fa fa-cash-register"></i>
                                    <div class="cmp-nfc-wave"></div>
                                    <div class="cmp-nfc-wave"></div>
                                    <div class="cmp-nfc-wave"></div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-nfc-label" data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.visual_terminal">Payment Terminal</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-callout info">
                            <div class="cmp-callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-callout-body">
                                <strong data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.antenna_title">NFC Antenna Location</strong>
                                <p data-i18n="making_payments.nfc_tap.antenna_body">The NFC antenna is usually located at the top-center of the back of your phone.
                                    Remove thick phone cases if you're having trouble connecting. Check your device
                                    manufacturer's specs for exact antenna placement.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Section: Payment Confirmation -->
                    <section class="cmp-section" id="cmp_content_confirm">
                        <h2 class="cmp-section-title" id="payment-confirmation" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.heading">Payment Confirmation</h2>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.intro">After every successful payment, you'll receive an instant confirmation with transaction
                            details. This serves as your digital receipt.</p>
                        <h4 data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt_title">What's Included in Your Receipt</h4>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt_intro">Every payment confirmation includes the following details:</p>
                        <!-- Receipt Mock -->
                        <div class="cmp-receipt-mock" aria-label="Example payment receipt">
                            <div class="cmp-receipt-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-receipt-label" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.success">Payment Successful</div>
                            <div class="cmp-receipt-amount">XCG42.50</div>
                            <div class="cmp-receipt-label" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.merchant">Coffee House Downtown</div>
                            <div class="cmp-receipt-details">
                                <div class="cmp-receipt-row">
                                    <span class="label" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.transaction_id">Transaction ID</span>
                                    <span class="value">#MPY-2025-8A3F</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-receipt-row">
                                    <span class="label" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.datetime">Date & Time</span>
                                    <span class="value">Mar 11, 2025 • 2:34 PM</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-receipt-row">
                                    <span class="label" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.method">Payment Method</span>
                                    <span class="value">QR Code</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-receipt-row">
                                    <span class="label" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.status">Status</span>
                                    <span class="value" style="color: #22c55e; font-weight: 600;" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.completed">Completed</span>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-receipt-row">
                                    <span class="label" data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.receipt.balance">Wallet Balance</span>
                                    <span class="value">XCG 1,457.50</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-callout success">
                            <div class="cmp-callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-callout-body">
                                <strong data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.share_title">Share & Export Receipts</strong>
                                <p data-i18n-html="making_payments.confirmation.share_body">Tap the <strong>"Share"</strong> button on any receipt to send it via email,
                                    messaging apps, or save as a PDF. You can also export all receipts from the
                                    Transaction History section for accounting purposes.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <h4 data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.failed_title">Failed or Pending Payments</h4>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.confirmation.failed_intro">If a payment fails or remains pending, you'll see a different status screen:</p>
                        <ul style="margin: 12px 0 16px 20px; color: #334155; line-height: 1.8;">
                            <li data-i18n-html="making_payments.confirmation.failed_list.pending">
                                <strong style="color: #d97706;">Pending:</strong> The payment is being processed. This
                                usually resolves within 30 seconds. Don't retry until it resolves.
                            </li>
                            <li data-i18n-html="making_payments.confirmation.failed_list.failed">
                                <strong style="color: #dc2626;">Failed:</strong> The payment could not be completed.
                                Check your balance, internet connection, and try again. No money is deducted for failed
                                transactions.
                            </li>
                            <li data-i18n-html="making_payments.confirmation.failed_list.refunded">
                                <strong style="color: #2563eb;">Refunded:</strong> The merchant initiated a refund.
                                Funds return to your wallet within 1-3 business days.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Section: Payment History -->
                    <section class="cmp-section" id="cmp_content_history">
                        <h2 class="cmp-section-title" id="payment-history" data-i18n="making_payments.history.heading">Transaction History</h2>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.history.intro">Track all your past payments in one place. Your transaction history keeps a complete record
                            of every payment you&apos;ve made through the mPay Consumer Wallet.</p>
                        <h4 data-i18n="making_payments.history.access_title">Accessing Your History</h4>
                        <p data-i18n-html="making_payments.history.access_body">Navigate to <strong>Home → Transactions</strong> or swipe up on the home screen. You can
                            filter transactions by date range, payment method, status, or merchant name.</p>
                        <h4 data-i18n="making_payments.history.sample_title">Sample Transaction History</h4>
                        <div class="cmp-history-table-wrapper">
                            <table class="cmp-history-table" aria-label="Sample transaction history">
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.date">Date</th>
                                        <th data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.merchant">Merchant</th>
                                        <th data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.method">Method</th>
                                        <th data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.amount">Amount</th>
                                        <th data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.status">Status</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Mar 11, 2025</td>
                                        <td>Coffee House Downtown</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-method-icon"><i class="fa fa-qrcode"></i> <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.method_qr">QR Code</span></span>
                                        </td>
                                        <td>XCG 42.50</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-status-badge completed"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.completed">Completed</span></span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Mar 10, 2025</td>
                                        <td>QuickMart Grocery</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-method-icon"><i class="fa fa-wifi"></i> <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.method_nfc">NFC</span></span></td>
                                        <td>XCG 128.75</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-status-badge completed"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.completed">Completed</span></span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Mar 10, 2025</td>
                                        <td>Metro Gas Station</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-method-icon"><i class="fa fa-qrcode"></i> <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.method_qr">QR Code</span></span>
                                        </td>
                                        <td>XCG 55.00</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-status-badge completed"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.completed">Completed</span></span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Mar 9, 2025</td>
                                        <td>TechShop Online</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-method-icon"><i class="fa fa-qrcode"></i> <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.method_qr">QR Code</span></span>
                                        </td>
                                        <td>XCG 299.99</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-status-badge pending"><i class="fa fa-clock"></i>
                                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.pending">Pending</span></span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Mar 8, 2025</td>
                                        <td>City Pharmacy</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-method-icon"><i class="fa fa-wifi"></i> <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.method_nfc">NFC</span></span></td>
                                        <td>XCG 18.30</td>
                                        <td><span class="cmp-status-badge completed"><i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.history.table.completed">Completed</span></span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-callout info">
                            <div class="cmp-callout-icon">
                                <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-callout-body">
                                <strong data-i18n="making_payments.history.export_title">Export Your Data</strong>
                                <p data-i18n-html="making_payments.history.export_body">You can export your transaction history as CSV or PDF by tapping the
                                    <strong>"Export"</strong> button at the top of the Transactions screen. Choose a
                                    date range and file format.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Payment Flow Screenshots -->
                    <section class="cmp-screenshots-section" id="cmp_screenshots">
                        <h2 class="cmp-section-title" id="payment-flow" data-i18n="making_payments.overview.heading">Payment Flow Overview</h2>
                        <p data-i18n="making_payments.overview.intro">Here's a visual walkthrough of the complete payment process from start to finish.</p>
                        <div class="cmp-screenshots-grid">
                            <div class="cmp-screenshot-card">
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-image">
                                    <span class="cmp-screenshot-step-badge">Step 1</span>
                                    <i class="fa fa-hand-pointer"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-caption" data-i18n="making_payments.overview.steps.1">Tap "Pay" on home screen</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-screenshot-card">
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-image">
                                    <span class="cmp-screenshot-step-badge">Step 2</span>
                                    <i class="fa fa-qrcode"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-caption" data-i18n="making_payments.overview.steps.2">Choose QR scan or NFC tap</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-screenshot-card">
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-image">
                                    <span class="cmp-screenshot-step-badge">Step 3</span>
                                    <i class="fa fa-camera"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-caption" data-i18n="making_payments.overview.steps.3">Scan merchant QR code</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-screenshot-card">
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-image">
                                    <span class="cmp-screenshot-step-badge">Step 4</span>
                                    <i class="fa fa-dollar-sign"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-caption" data-i18n="making_payments.overview.steps.4">Review payment amount</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-screenshot-card">
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-image">
                                    <span class="cmp-screenshot-step-badge">Step 5</span>
                                    <i class="fa fa-fingerprint"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-caption" data-i18n="making_payments.overview.steps.5">Authenticate with biometrics</div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cmp-screenshot-card">
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-image">
                                    <span class="cmp-screenshot-step-badge">Step 6</span>
                                    <i class="fa fa-check-circle"></i>
                                </div>
                                <div class="cmp-screenshot-caption" data-i18n="making_payments.overview.steps.6">Payment confirmed!</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- FAQ Section -->
                    <section class="cmp-faq-section" id="cmp_faq_accordion">
                        <h2 class="cmp-section-title" id="faq" data-i18n="making_payments.faq.heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                        <div class="cmp-faq-item">
                            <button class="cmp-faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-1">
                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.faq.q1">What's the maximum amount I can pay per transaction?</span>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
                            </button>
                            <div class="cmp-faq-answer" id="faq-answer-1" role="region">
                                <div class="cmp-faq-answer-inner" data-i18n-html="making_payments.faq.a1">
                                    The default transaction limit is $5,000 per payment. Verified accounts (KYC Level 2)
                                    can request higher limits up to $25,000 per transaction. You can view and manage
                                    your limits in <strong>Settings → Payment Limits</strong>.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-faq-item">
                            <button class="cmp-faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-2">
                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.faq.q2">Can I pay without an internet connection?</span>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
                            </button>
                            <div class="cmp-faq-answer" id="faq-answer-2" role="region">
                                <div class="cmp-faq-answer-inner" data-i18n-html="making_payments.faq.a2">
                                    NFC payments can work in offline mode for small transactions (under $50) if you have
                                    pre-authorized offline payments in your settings. QR code payments always require an
                                    active internet connection to process. Offline payments sync once you're back
                                    online.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-faq-item">
                            <button class="cmp-faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-3">
                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.faq.q3">What should I do if the QR scanner doesn't recognize the code?</span>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
                            </button>
                            <div class="cmp-faq-answer" id="faq-answer-3" role="region">
                                <div class="cmp-faq-answer-inner" data-i18n-html="making_payments.faq.a3">
                                    First, ensure you have adequate lighting and hold your camera steady. Clean your
                                    camera lens if it's smudged. If the QR code appears damaged or faded, ask the
                                    merchant to generate a fresh code. You can also try entering the merchant's payment
                                    ID manually by tapping "Enter Code Manually" below the scanner.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-faq-item">
                            <button class="cmp-faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-4">
                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.faq.q4">Is NFC payment supported on all devices?</span>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
                            </button>
                            <div class="cmp-faq-answer" id="faq-answer-4" role="region">
                                <div class="cmp-faq-answer-inner" data-i18n-html="making_payments.faq.a4">
                                    NFC payments require a device with an NFC chip. Most Android phones manufactured
                                    after 2018 and all iPhones from iPhone 7 onwards support NFC. You can check
                                    compatibility in <strong>Settings → Payment Methods → NFC Status</strong>. If your
                                    device doesn't support NFC, you can still use QR code payments.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-faq-item">
                            <button class="cmp-faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-5">
                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.faq.q5">Are there any fees for making payments?</span>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
                            </button>
                            <div class="cmp-faq-answer" id="faq-answer-5" role="region">
                                <div class="cmp-faq-answer-inner" data-i18n-html="making_payments.faq.a5">
                                    MPay Consumer Wallet does not charge any fees for making payments to merchants. The
                                    payment processing fee is handled on the merchant's side. P2P transfers may have a
                                    small fee depending on your account tier — check the <a
                                        onclick="load_page('consumer_p2p_transfers')"
                                        style="color: #2563eb; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: underline;">P2P
                                        Transfers</a> documentation for details.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cmp-faq-item">
                            <button class="cmp-faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-6">
                                <span data-i18n="making_payments.faq.q6">Can I cancel a payment after it's been sent?</span>
                                <i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i>
                            </button>
                            <div class="cmp-faq-answer" id="faq-answer-6" role="region">
                                <div class="cmp-faq-answer-inner" data-i18n-html="making_payments.faq.a6">
                                    Completed payments cannot be cancelled directly. You'll need to contact the merchant
                                    and request a refund through the MPay system. If you believe a payment was
                                    unauthorized, go to <strong>Transactions → Select Transaction → Report
                                        Issue</strong> to initiate a dispute. Our support team responds within 24 hours.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <!-- Prev / Next Navigation -->
                    <nav class="cmp-prev-next" id="cmp_prev_next" aria-label="Page navigation">
                        <a class="cmp-prev-next-link prev" onclick="load_page('consumer_account_setup')" tabindex="0">
